Upstream attribution
====================

The reference documentation under `references/` and the setup script under
`scripts/setup.sh` in this sub-skill are vendored verbatim from the
`manim-video` sub-skill of the `browser-use/video-use` project.

Source:
    https://github.com/browser-use/video-use
    Path:   skills/manim-video/
    Cloned: 2026-05-06

The upstream README (`README.md` at the repo root) describes the project as
"100% open source." However, at the time of vendoring no formal `LICENSE`,
`COPYING`, or `NOTICE` file was present in the upstream repository, and
`pyproject.toml` did not declare an SPDX identifier. We therefore cannot
assert a specific license (e.g. MIT) for these vendored files on the
upstream's behalf.

Action for downstream users / redistributors:
- Treat the vendored content as "all rights reserved by the original
  authors" until upstream publishes an explicit license, and consult the
  current state of https://github.com/browser-use/video-use before
  redistribution outside this skill bundle.
- New files added in this sub-skill (SKILL.md, install.md, pyproject.toml,
  this file) follow the license of the parent `agentic-frame` project.

If the upstream adds a LICENSE file, replace the contents of this file with
that license verbatim and update the attribution paragraph in `SKILL.md`.
